message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in Kiribati in the past five years was the announcement made by the President of Kiribati, Taneti Maamau, in 2019 regarding the purchase of land in Fiji. The government of Kiribati purchased 20 square kilometers of land on the island of Vanua Levu in Fiji, as a potential refuge for its citizens in the face of rising sea levels and the threat of climate change. This decision highlighted the grave concerns Kiribati faces due to its low-lying geography and the potential displacement of its population in the future. The purchase of land in Fiji was seen as a proactive step towards ensuring the safety and security of Kiribati's people in the face of climate change impacts.
